_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:330:                        f\"Partial dynamic-access coverage for {class_name} \"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:459:        \"\"\"Regenerate the dynamic-access report after the gate to reflect new coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:479:        \"\"\"Start resumable chunking when the first dynamic-access report is too large.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:501:            \"Large dynamic-access report detected; starting large-library series \"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:728:                \"Coverage report loaded but contains no usable dynamic-access guidance:\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:804:        log_stage(\"dynamic-access\", message)\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:808:        log_stage(\"dynamic-access\", message, indent_level=indent_level)\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:142:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:145:            \"When using dynamic-access strategies, keep generated tests even when they do not improve \"\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:146:            \"dynamic-access coverage.\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:152:        help=\"Enable resumable large-library chunking for dynamic-access workflows.\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:6:\"\"\"Workflow entry point for improving dynamic-access coverage on an existing library.\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:9:focuses solely on generating new tests to improve dynamic-access coverage.\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:73:        description=\"Improve dynamic-access coverage for an existing library version.\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:112:        help=\"Enable resumable large-library chunking for dynamic-access workflows.\",\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:319:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n./tests/src/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-launcher/1.11.3/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = org.junit.platform:junit-platform-launcher:1.11.3\n./tests/src/org.springframework/spring-jcl/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_jcl/LogAdapterTest.java:16:    private static final String LOGGER_NAME = \"spring-jcl.dynamic-access\";\n./tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org_jboss_logmanager/jboss_logmanager/Formatters12Test.java:51:                \"Anonymous privileged-action construction is only needed for JVM dynamic-access coverage\");\n./tests/src/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/4.10.4/src/test/java/org_apache_lucene/lucene_core/RamUsageEstimatorTest.java:39:        BytesRef bytesRef = new BytesRef(\"dynamic-access\");\n./tests/src/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_lucene/lucene_core/RamUsageEstimatorTest.java:39:        BytesRef bytesRef = new BytesRef(\"dynamic-access\");\n./tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_streams/IntegrationTestUtilsDynamicAccessTest.java:67:        builder.stream(\"dynamic-access-input\").to(\"dynamic-access-output\");\n./tests/src/io.projectreactor/reactor-core/3.5.1/src/test/java/io_projectreactor/reactor_core/TracesTest.java:20:                .checkpoint(\"dynamic-access-traces\", true)\n./tests/src/io.projectreactor/reactor-core/3.5.1/src/test/java